title: 3 Husky paws UP!
text:
I have three Siberian Huskies that are VORACIOUS Chicken/Rawhide eaters. Of all the treats I have ever come across, its the Chicken wrapped rawhide that is their absolute favorite. Several different companies offer them, but I am always on the lookout for a new offering. Came across "A Heart for Paws" from Black Mountain Supply on my last Amazon search and since they were all natural and coming from my home state of Idaho, I ordered a package for testing. Well, I am here to say my 3 huskies LOVED THEM. They powered through a package of them in no time at all.
The only negative thing I would say is that I wish they offered this in a BIGGER version. Huskies generally run in the 35-50lb range, and I would say these treats are on the smallish side for a dog that size. They were easily able to CRUNCH right through the entire stick in a couple minutes, rather than having to CHEW/GNAW there way through the rawhide. NOT a fault of the manufacturer, just need a BIGGER sized option. But the Doggoes LOVED THEM and I will get more of them.
